    "body": "Thanks. There is a difference though, I do not think in your second example the event is broadcasted as `0>0` is always false.\r\n\r\nIn your second example, simply the body of the function is not executed, while using `require` will actually abort execution with the `revert` opcode, which is not supported yet, hence it ends up as an invalid code. The result of invalid opcode is pretty much the same and this is intended. Once `revert` is supported, `require` will cost less as it will not consume all the remainder gas, but still abort.",
